# UI/UX Guidelines for PiperWorkbench

## Design Philosophy

Professional audio workbench with clear affordance for voice processing, analysis, and synthesis. Familiarity with DAW (Digital Audio Workstation) conventions where applicable.

## Layout

### Main Window Structure
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ File Edit View Help                  [_][=][×] │
├──────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ [Play] [Stop] [Record] | ▶ ◼ □ [Speaker] │
├──────────────────────────────────────────┤
│      │                   │                 │
│ Proj │   Waveform View   │   Parameters    │
│ Files│   (center focus)  │   & Controls    │
│      │                   │                 │
│      │   Spectrum (zoom) │   Presets       │
├──────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Status: Ready | Sample Rate: 22050Hz | Duration: 0:00 │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Color Scheme

- **Background**: Dark theme (reduces eye strain for long sessions)
- **Waveform**: Bright accent (cyan/blue) on dark background
- **Spectrum**: Heat map (blue → green → red)
- **Controls**: Subtle grays with highlights on interaction

## Interaction Patterns

### Playback
- Play/Stop buttons (big, obvious)
- Scrubber bar for timeline navigation
- Speed/pitch indicators
- Loop region selection (drag on waveform)

### Voice Parameters
- **TTS Controls**: Voice selection, pitch range, speed
- **EQ**: 3-band or parametric (depends on phase)
- **Filters**: Low/high-pass, resonance
- **Synth**: Oscillator waveform, envelope (ADSR)
- **Modulation**: LFO depth/rate, tremolo, vibrato

### Analysis
- Waveform viewer (zoom/pan)
- Spectrum analyzer (FFT display, frequency axis)
- Phoneme timeline (when implemented)

## Accessibility

- High contrast mode option
- Keyboard shortcuts for all major functions
- Tooltips on hover (control descriptions)
- Consistent icon set (Material Design or similar)

## Responsive Design

- Resizable panels (drag dividers)
- Remember window size/position on close
- Adaptable to small (1280x720) and large (4K) displays
- Touch-friendly button sizes (minimum 44x44px for touch targets)

## State & Persistence

- Auto-save current project state
- Recent projects menu
- Undo/redo history (UI actions + audio processing)
- Preference panels (theme, audio device, paths)

## Prototype Milestones

1. **Alpha** (Phase 1-2): Functional layout, waveform display, basic controls
2. **Beta** (Phase 3-4): All audio tools integrated, professional appearance
3. **Release** (Phase 5): Polish, accessibility audit, user testing feedback incorporated
